🛠️ Task 1 – Essential Commands

Run each command and note what it does.

ps

Lists processes attached to the current terminal.

ps -ef

Shows all running processes.

ps aux

Displays CPU, memory, user, and command details.

top

Shows live system resource usage.

If available:

htop

Install if needed:

sudo apt install htop
🛠️ Task 2 – Process Monitoring

Check CPU usage:

top

Check memory usage:

free -h

Check uptime:

uptime

Load average:

cat /proc/loadavg
🛠️ Task 3 – Start Background Processes

Run:

sleep 300 &

Find it:

ps -ef | grep sleep

Display background jobs:

jobs

Bring it back to the foreground:

fg

Stop it with:

Ctrl + C
🛠️ Task 4 – Kill Processes

Start another process:

sleep 600 &

Find its PID:

ps -ef | grep sleep

Kill it gracefully:

kill PID

Force kill:

kill -9 PID

Kill by name:

pkill sleep

or

killall sleep
🛠️ Task 5 – Process Priority

Start:

sleep 500 &

Check priority:

ps -el

Lower priority:

nice -n 10 sleep 500

Change priority:

renice 5 PID
